    &lt;CommentText&gt;I have been having regular colonoscopies since 1995 various hospitals in the UK, Braxil, Peru and this was the best experience so far. As I live 100 metres from the South Entrance of the Hospital The facilities at Solihull are much better than the hospital I was attending previously, and in future I wish that my examinations will all be in Solihull Hospital under the doctor I had this time.  
The only thing with the appointment was that I had to wait 1.45 hrs in the waiting room before the session commenced.  
I had no after effects or bleeding and left the hospital after 2 hours.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
